Bronstein et al., used giant CdSe/CdS QDs in an LSC cavity (Fig. 5
                     ) [49,72]. PLMA/QD composite (30 μm) was placed between two thin glass films. A mc-Si solar cell (0.15 



                                 mm


                                 2



                     ) was placed inside the structure acting as light detector. The LSC cavity could achieve 30-fold solar concentration (C) and ∼82% waveguide efficiency. Escape cone losses decreased due to the boosted trapping efficiency and the calculated PCE significantly increased from 10.35% to 54.37%. A similar test was performed for an LSC with a trench reflector covered by the photonic mirror where PCE increased to 77.38%. Note that PCE was calculated by using the measured output power density, AM1.5G input solar radiation energy (1000 W m−2) and Eq (5).
